      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(firecrawl): add keyless Firecrawl Search (Free) provider + richer firecrawl_search options",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFirecrawl `web_fetch`/`firecrawl_scrape` already support hosted **keyless** starter access (PR #93590), but `web_search` still hard-required a Firecrawl API key — so OpenClaw could fetch pages out-of-the-box but could not search the web without a key. The hosted `/v2/search` endpoint accepts the same unauthenticated starter requests as `/v2/scrape` (verified: `POST https://api.firecrawl.dev/v2/search` with no `Authorization` header returns `200` + results).\n\nThe explicit `firecrawl_search` tool was also missing several first-class `/v2/search` knobs (domain filters, time filter, geo-targeting) and capped `count` at 10 vs the API's 100.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nSearch queries are sensitive, so the maintainers deliberately keep keyless **search** opt-in (core `allowKeylessAutoSelect: false` for search; `parallel-free` is a distinct, never-auto-detected provider). This PR mirrors that exact convention for Firecrawl rather than changing core behavior:\n\n- Adds a second web_search provider **`firecrawl-free`** (\"Firecrawl Search (Free)\") — `requiresCredential: false`, **no `autoDetectOrder`**, opt-in only. It calls `/v2/search` with `access: \"keyless\"` (no `Authorization` header).\n- The keyed **`firecrawl`** provider is unchanged (auto-detected when a key is present). The explicit `firecrawl_search` tool still requires a key. Core `runtime-web-tools.ts` is untouched.\n- `firecrawl-free` is registered everywhere the keyed provider / `parallel-free` are: `index.ts`, the `web-search-provider` barrel, the `web-search-contract-api` metadata artifact (the onboarding/setup source), manifest contracts, the official-external plugin catalog snapshot, and the doctor/contract registries.\n\nAlso brings `firecrawl_search` to parity with `/v2/search`: `includeDomains`/`excludeDomains` (mutually exclusive), `tbs`, `location`, `country`, and `count` raised to 100.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- A new opt-in **\"Firecrawl Search (Free)\"** option appears in onboarding / `openclaw configure --section web`; selecting it enables web_search with **no API key** (add a key via the keyed provider for higher limits).\n- Keyless search is **never auto-selected** — users explicitly choose it, so queries are only sent to the free tier on opt-in.\n- Existing keyed users and other providers are unaffected; no config migration required.\n- `firecrawl_search` gains domain/time/location filters and up to 100 results.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Live: keyless `POST /v2/search` returns `200` + results.\n- Provider code path: `createFirecrawlFreeWebSearchProvider().createTool().execute({query})` with no `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` returns real, security-wrapped results.\n- Onboarding: `configure --section web` shows \"Firecrawl Search (Free)\", prompts for no key, writes `provider: \"firecrawl-free\"` (screenshot).\n- Tests: `firecrawl-tools.test.ts` (keyless free provider, key-required keyed/tool paths, domain/time/location forwarding, include/exclude mutual exclusion), `runtime-web-tools.test.ts`, registry contract + doctor migrate tests pass.\n- tsgo core+extensions+ext-tests clean; oxlint + oxfmt + docs-format clean.\n",
        "branch": "feat/firecrawl-keyless-search",
